# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
#
# Intentionally empty.
#
# Cross-host redirects (pages.dev -> apex, www -> apex) are handled by
# Cloudflare Redirect Rules at Rules -> Redirect Rules in the dashboard.
# Those rules are evaluated at the edge before the request reaches Pages,
# and they work for cross-hostname sources/destinations that the _redirects
# file format rejects.
#
# If you ever need same-host redirects (e.g. /old-page -> /new-page),
# add them here using relative paths only:
#     /old-page /new-page 301
# (No scheme/hostname in the source or destination.)
